data.reddit:
I posted something similar to this in 
r/TooAfraidToAsk
But here’s all the relevant details: 

I am not diabetic. I get bloodwork done annually because diabetes runs in my family and every time I bring up to my GP that I am constantly thirsty when he tells me my blood sugar is fine. 

I drink juice, Gatorade, plain water, and the occasional energy drink. I drink water all day long. I can’t leave the house without something to drink. 

I don’t sweat excessively, my pee is light yellow/sometimes clear. I have regular bowel movements. 

I’m not a teenager but still young, tall, moderate exercise, above average weight, poor diet (not in the junk food sense in the sense I eat maybe one large meal a day and then nothing else, working on that lol), get just under enough sleep. 

I am constantly thirsty. My body constantly craves water. Even minutes after drinking water I have severe cottonmouth and already have the urge to drink again. I drink so much water I squeeze in at least two gatorades a day so I’m staying actually hydrated and not just flushing my kidneys. I have a monster/five hour energy before work, usually juice with a meal. 

I do not vape, and only socially smoke cigarettes. A pack will last me a week, not as long if I’m drinking. 

What on earth could this be?? It’s been like this as long as I can remember.
